                            <comment id="17082364" author="garydgregory" created="Mon, 13 Apr 2020 14:44:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I would welcome a PR with unit tests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17082517" author="ottobackwards" created="Mon, 13 Apr 2020 17:39:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ggregory&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ggregory&quot;&gt;ggregory&lt;/a&gt; can you add me as an io contributor, I&apos;ll do a pr&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17082531" author="ottobackwards" created="Mon, 13 Apr 2020 17:56:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think this should be an IllegalArgumentException though&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17082543" author="michael-o" created="Mon, 13 Apr 2020 18:06:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=otto&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;otto&quot;&gt;otto&lt;/a&gt;, no. &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt; must always lead to &lt;tt&gt;NPE&lt;/tt&gt;. It is a common misconception to use &lt;tt&gt;IAE&lt;/tt&gt; for that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17082544" author="ottobackwards" created="Mon, 13 Apr 2020 18:07:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fair enough.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17082559" author="garydgregory" created="Mon, 13 Apr 2020 18:22:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Use the JRE&apos;s &lt;tt&gt;Objects.requireNonNull(foo, &quot;foo&quot;)&lt;/tt&gt; pattern.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
